gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: This dataset is a point shapefile of licensed cellular towers downloaded as part of the FCC ULS database of cellular towers in Indiana. The ground condition of this data changes frequently, therefore; new towers that may have been in the application process are not included in this dataset. The dataset does not represent all antennae structures.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: The files I_cell.zip and pa_ddef15 were downloaded from the FCC ULS website [http://wireless.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/wtb-datadump.pl] under the Cellular Towers section.

LO.DAT was imported into Excel and field names were added from "pa_ddef15" spreadsheet. The three fields for position degrees, minutes, and seconds were transformed to decimal degrees and the spreadsheet was saved as "dbase IV" format. The table was then added to an ArcMAP project and used to create a point file using the "create event theme" option. The file was then queried to create a subset consisting only of Indiana locations. Any fields which had no data present or served little purpose were deleted. A stepwise guide to this process is published in Trammell. S. 2001. "'Locate Cell Towers in Your County', ArcUser: April June 2001. ESRI. Pages 50-53."

This metadata file was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v. 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v. 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected.
spreadsheet defining all fields for all tables associated with ULS data.
Base text file containing all point coordinates and attributes.
